         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">Z. received a strongly negative response by the Mantua
                            community at large when his plans to travel to the Holy Land became
                            known. R. Hayyim Gavili and R. Juda Bariel reprimanded him that he
                            should not abandon his duties as spiritual leader and head of the local
                            yeshiva. He also learned from Kohen’s brother that his own community
                            likewise complains about his impending departure and they are angry at
                            Z. because he asked Kohen to accompany him. He exhorts Kohen to do like
                            him and to leave all non-essential duties aside.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">דרך איש ישר לפלם</note>
